explanation: This solution uses a stack to keep track of the opening brackets encountered so far. It iterates over the string, pushing opening brackets onto the stack and popping them off when a corresponding closing bracket is encountered. If a closing bracket does not match the top of the stack, or if there are unmatched opening brackets left at the end, the string is invalid. This approach has a high efficiency due to its constant time complexity for stack operations and a single pass through the string.

